## Bio

Dr. Hulshof studies biodiversity across spatial and temporal scales. Her research focuses on the forces that promote and inhibit biodiversity. She frequently collaborates with 
researchers who study computer vision and ecosystem modelling.
Her work has been funded by the National Science Foundation. 

## Education

**University of Arizona** | Tucson, AZ

Ph.D. in Ecology and Evolutionary Biology | Minor in Global Change | September 2007 - January 2013

**University of Pennsylvania** | Philadelphia, PA

B.A. in Biology and Chemistry | September 2002 - May 2006

## Experience

**Virginia Commonwealth University** | Assistant Professor | January 2018 - Present

**University of Puerto Rico Mayaguez** | Assistant Professor | September 2014 - December 2017
